  "title": "Shepherd's Pie",
  "body": "Originally a thrift dish for using up the Sunday roast. Beef makes 'cottage pie'; lamb makes 'shepherd's.'\n\n· 1½ lb ground lamb (or leftover roast lamb, diced)\n· 1 large onion, chopped\n· 2 carrots, diced\n· 1 cup peas\n· 2 tablespoons flour\n· 1½ cups beef or lamb stock\n· 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce\n· Salt, pepper, sprig of thyme\n· 2 lb potatoes, peeled\n· ½ cup milk\n· 4 tablespoons butter",
